        <p>


	<p>Pecans are naturally delicious, nutritious and versatile food. Their rich, nutty flavor ensures good eating right from the shell, provides a special touch to simple dishes, and adds elegance to traditional recipes. For Centuries, pecans have been used in sweet baked goods, candies, and holiday treats, served buttered, sugared, spiced, or salted... mixed into salads, vegetables, entrees, and desserts.</p>
	<p>Flavorful pecans make a healthy between-meal snack. Pecans contain unsaturated fat, the kind your body needs and utilizes. Pecans are a good source of protein and important vitamins and minerals, including iron, calcium, B vitamins, rich in potassium and phosphorus. Pecans provide fiber, which is so important in todays diet.</p>
	<p>Pecans are enjoyed year-round and will hold freshness 2 years frozen, or about 1 year kept air tight refrigerated. Don’t save them only for holiday baking! Keep a <a href=products.htm>supply of pecans</a> on hand for use anytime. Fun to eat. <a href=contact.htm>BUY SOME NOW!</a></p>

